  <p style="margin-top:1.5rem">
    <strong>Why this matters:</strong> <code>setHTML()</code> makes sanitization
    an intrinsic browser behaviour — there's nothing for developers to forget.
    Combined with a Lit directive, this could replace <code>unsafeHTML</code> entirely
    for contexts where Trusted Types isn't required.
  </p>

